text:
SCIALATIELLI. I dont know how to pronounce it, but every single time i go to vegas, i stop by DOCG and get my favorite pasta in the whole wide world. the SCIALATIELLI. its a pasta dish cooked to PERFECTION with abundance of lobster and shrimp. For an italian dish, it is on te spicy side but thats the best thing about it. I have to have hot sauce with every meal, steak, spagetthi, pizza, sushi, burgers, rice, whatver it is, i want hot sauce, and need hot sauce or some sort of condiment. BUT THIS? o m g. best dish ever. i dont need hot sauce, i dont need ketchup, i dont want salt or pepper. its heaven in a dish. 

if youve been here and havnt tried this dish? I feel sorry for you. :( 
if you're planning on visiting vegas and you want italian? come grab a bite of scialatielli!
